            "answer_text": "This answer is in Indian context: Since Indian engineering curriculum is 40 years old hence NO Indian engineering college produces any skilled-employable Cloud Computing professional. Hence there is NO serious Cloud Computing companies in India. Cloud Computing happens primarily in the developed countries. Hence there is NO accurate answer to this question.  To become a cloud computing professional you need to put in about 6000\u20138000 hours(or 6\u20138 years) of self hardwork. It is an engineering arena of computer science hence NO such engineering happens in Indian because Indian engineering curriculum is 40 years old and NO such serious cloud computing companies are there in India. Serious Tip: Make several kinds of Operating Systems and several kinds of Web Browser and put it on your github profile to be able to impress some cloud computing professional in some developed countries. All the other ways to reliably become a cloud computing professional are a subset of what I am suggesting. A cloud computing professional primarily does a subset of these two kinds of projects while working as a cloud computing professional !!! ",
