            "answer_text": "It\u2019s all going to depend on what country you are in and what tier city the company is based on. The fact is the cost of living plays the vital role when companies decide the pay scale of their employees and it usually varies from one state to another. I know people that left the tier 3 cities and got more hike in tier 2 and tier 1 city, but in other places, the pay scale of tier 3 city might be a decent long-term level to be looking at. The salary figures mentioned in the above post might be the benchmark, but I guess companies will consider the certifications / experience, etc\u2026 So in my opinion, the best way to determine what the entry level package in Cloud is to simply apply your resume in some leading cloud hosting companies in the India. ",
